# Coding Conventions

> Index of project conventions. Each convention lives in its own file so the
> agent can load only what's relevant to the current task.

| Convention | File | Enforced by |
|---|---|---|
| Naming | `naming.md` | linter + `check-architecture.sh` |
| Error handling | `error-handling.md` | unit tests + linter |
| Testing | `testing.md` | `check-tests.sh` (Gate 3) |
| Logging | `logging.md` | linter (`no-console` rule) |
| API calls | (add as needed) | custom linter rule |

## How to add a new convention

1. Write the rule as a sentence in a new file under `docs/conventions/`.
2. If CI can check it, write the check (`scripts/check-*.sh` or a linter rule).
3. Add a row to the table above.

If a rule can't be mechanically checked, it's a Guideline — put it in a
separate section so agents know it's soft.

